<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1171,2010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,345,1248,1274]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description</emphasis>
. Sponge insinuating inside two fragments, 
<number box="[869,884,1249,1275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
<date box="[892,930,1249,1275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
x 
<number box="[915,930,1249,1275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
<date box="[939,977,1249,1275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
x 
<quantity box="[962,977,1249,1275]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="cm" value="2.0">2</quantity>
</date>
cm and 
<number box="[1081,1096,1249,1275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
<date box="[1105,1143,1249,1275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
x 
<number box="[1128,1143,1249,1275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
x 
<quantity box="[1174,1260,1249,1275]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="cm" value="0.5">0.5 cm</quantity>
, of an original single piece of coral covered on the outside by 
<taxonomicName authority="Hechtel, 1965" authorityName="Hechtel" authorityYear="1965" box="[736,1249,1288,1314]" class="Demospongiae" family="Spirastrellidae" genus="Diplastrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="megastellata">
<emphasis box="[736,1047,1288,1313]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diplastrella megastellata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hechtel" box="[1065,1240,1288,1314]" pageId="3" pageNumber="37" refString="Hechtel, G. J. (1965) A Systematic study of the Demospongiae of Port Royal, Jamaica. Bulletin of the Peabody Museum of Natural History, 20, 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1965">
Hechtel, 
<number box="[1178,1240,1288,1314]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1266,1432,1288,1314]" class="Demospongiae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="order">Hadromerida</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,336,1326,1352]" class="Demospongiae" family="Spirastrellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Spirastrellidae</taxonomicName>
). No traces of the sponge were detected on the upper/outer side of the coral, but inside it several corridors and holes of approx. 
<quantity box="[616,685,1365,1391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
diameter and 
<quantity box="[858,972,1365,1391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5–10 mm</quantity>
long are filled with tissues of the new species. Live color not noted, beige colored in alcohol. Consistency soft.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1171,2010]" box="[197,745,1442,1468]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,305,1442,1468]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Skeleton</emphasis>
. Confused, no apparent organization.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1171,2010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,304,1480,1506]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Spicules</emphasis>
. Mesotriaenes (dichomesotriaenes, mesocalthrops), small amphitriaenes, oxea-like spicules, amphiasters, microrhabds. Measurements presented here are based on 
<number box="[986,1015,1520,1546]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="10.0">10</number>
spicules instead of 
<number box="[1251,1283,1520,1546]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="25.0">25</number>
, due to large variability of shape and sizes of the various 
<typeStatus box="[667,733,1558,1584]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">types</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
